 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of a record of observations that have been made about an environment.
   </p>
   <p>
     Typical observations include, the product that was operating in the environment,
     observed climatic conditions such as temperature and humidity, the location where the 
     observations were made.
   </p>
   <p>
     The record, 
     represented by an 
     <express_ref
       linkend="product_environment_observed:arm:Product_environment_observed_arm.Observed_environment"/>,
     may be measured observations of a predefined environment, 
     represented by an 
     <express_ref linkend="product_environment_definition:arm:Product_environment_definition_arm.Environment_definition"/>,
     in which case the
     record is related back to the definition of a typical environment by
     <express_ref linkend="product_environment_observed:arm:Product_environment_observed_arm.Observed_environment_to_definition"/>.
   </p>
 </purpose>

